TI  - Familial breast cancer in Iceland.
PG  - 365-71
AB  - Women who have relatives known to have had breast cancer are at an increased risk 
      of getting the disease compared with the general population. On the basis of an 
      extensive collection of family trees of women with breast cancer, the magnitude 
      of this increase in risk is computed. Previously published results on other 
      breast cancer risk factors are drawn upon and it has been possible to take 
      account of some of these e.g., age, decade of birth, age at first childbirth and 
      parity in the risk estimates. The relative risk with such adjustment is found to 
      be 2.59 for mothers and 2.56 for sisters.
