DP  - 1988 Jun
TI  - "Telling bad news": physicians and the disclosure of undesirable information.
PG  - 109-32
AB  - To address the issue of what physicians tell patients, and how they arrive at 
      that decision, this report focuses on a single episode in breast cancer--the 
      event of telling the patient for the first time that she has cancer. This is a 
      participant-observation account of 118 events, framed from the physicians' 
      perspective. It describes how the 17 surgeons at the Breast Cancer Clinic 
      developed, organized and implemented their disclosure policies, and what 
      strategies they utilized to routinize a task they defined as difficult and 
      unpleasant.
