TI  - Breast cancer at Hiroshima and Nagasaki.
PG  - 209-10
AB  - A calculation is made of the incidence of breast cancer at Hiroshima and Nagasaki 
      using the dosimetry of Straume and Dobson. Gamma rays cause a mutation in a 
      critical gene. Using a two hit theory, an estimate of the number of target cells 
      and a time period of 24 years, an estimate of the probability of carcinogenesis 
      is obtained which is in good agreement with observation.
