DP  - 1985 Sep
TI  - C-band heteromorphism in breast cancer patients.
PG  - 37-42
AB  - The pattern of heteromorphism in the C-band-positive constitutive heterochromatin 
      of human chromosomes #1, #9, and #16 was studied in peripheral lymphocytes of 54 
      breast cancer patients and 78 control individuals. The parameters of the 
      heterochromatic regions analyzed were relative size, symmetry-asymmetry within 
      homologous pairs, and prevalence of inversions. Significant differences between 
      the two groups were found in C-band size of chromosomes #1, #9, and #16 and in 
      incidence of inversions on chromosomes #1 and #9. Significant differences were 
      noted between premenopausal and postmenopausal cancer patients in regard to 
      inversions on chromosome #9 and between familial and sporadic patients in regard 
      to C-band size on chromosome #16.
