DP  - 1984
TI  - Do infiltrative and anaplastic growth patterns alternate with season in human 
      breast cancer?
PG  - 156-9
AB  - The presence/absence of stromal metachromasia, at the zone of host-tumour 
      interaction, was recorded in 220 primary breast carcinomas. This reaction, which 
      is associated with an infiltrative as opposed to an expansive growth form, was 
      more common in primaries removed in the first half of the year than the second. 
      This adds to previous evidence based on histological grading that growth 
      synchronization has occurred in breast carcinomas in this district.
