DP  - 1988 Feb
TI  - c-Ha-ras-1 polymorphism in human breast carcinomas: evidence for a normal 
      distribution of alleles.
PG  - 245-50
AB  - Analysis of the c-Ha-ras-1 locus for restriction fragment length polymorphism was 
      determined by Southern blot hybridization in 112 specimens of primary breast 
      carcinoma. Normal cell samples were lymphocytes obtained from 61 of these breast 
      cancer patients and from 62 healthy donors. Our data indicate that the 
      distribution of c-Ha-ras-1 alleles in breast carcinoma patients did not 
      significantly differ from that found in normal individuals. In addition the loss 
      of one allele detected in 5 tumor samples was not correlated to the 
      aggressiveness of breast cancer. Consequently our data imply that hereditary 
      predisposition to breast cancer is not associated with the c-Ha-ras-1 
      polymorphism as previously reported.
