AB  - With increasing options for adjuvant therapy in breast cancer, it is even more 
      important to know which patients are at risk for recurrent disease. Variables 
      such as tumor size and node status are well-established markers. Others have 
      recently been proposed. Will these new markers improve our ability to assess 
      prognosis and select appropriate management modalities?
