VI  - 44
IP  - 2
DP  - 1989 Aug 15
TI  - Polymorphism of the c-Ha-ras-1 proto-oncogene in sporadic and familial breast 
      cancer.
PG  - 251-5
AB  - Two studies on breast cancer patients are described. Our aim was to examine 
      whether the combined frequency of rare c-Ha-ras-1 alleles in cancer patients was 
      raised. Firstly, the c-Ha-ras-1 locus in 56 breast cancer patients and 48 
      controls was examined for restriction fragment length polymorphism (RFLP) by 
      Southern blot analysis of leukocyte DNA. Four predominant allelic fragments were 
      found in both groups together with a variety of rare alleles. The 2 groups did 
      not differ significantly in overall distribution of c-Ha-ras-1 alleles. Rare 
      alleles combined were about as frequent in cases (7.1%) as in controls (6.3%). 
      Secondly, 53 members of 3 families having a high incidence of breast cancer were 
      c-Ha-ras-1 genotyped. None of 10 affected members was found to carry a rare 
      c-Ha-ras-1 allele. The only c-Ha-ras-1 allele common to 11 affected members was a 
      6.8-kb allele which is found in 72% of the controls. Furthermore, this allele was 
      found with equal frequency in affected and non-affected family members.
