DP  - 1988 Feb
TI  - Genetically determined polymorphism of the circulating human breast 
      cancer-associated DF3 antigen.
PG  - 436-40
AB  - The murine monoclonal antibody (MAb) DF3 was prepared against a human breast 
      carcinoma. Previous studies have demonstrated that DF3 antigen levels are 
      elevated in plasma of patients with breast cancer. Furthermore, MAb DF3 reacts 
      with circulating glycoproteins of different molecular weights ranging from 
      approximately 300 to 450 kd. The present study demonstrates that plasma DF3 
      antigen is comprised of at least four moieties with slow (S), intermediate (I), 
      rapid (R) and very rapid (VR) electrophoretic mobilities. The electrophoretic 
      mobility patterns for circulating DF3 antigen differ among individuals. Moreover, 
      DF3 antigen is detectable in urine, and the electrophoretic mobility of the 
      urinary moieties is similar, but not identical, to that in the plasma. Studies in 
      family members suggest that the electrophoretic heterogeneity of plasma DF3 
      antigen is determined by codominant expression of multiple alleles at a single 
      locus. This locus may code for the core protein of DF3 antigen. These findings 
      thus identify a genetically determined polymorphism of a circulating 
      tumor-associated glycoprotein.
