VI  - 103
IP  - 899
DP  - 1990 Oct 10
TI  - Breast cancer incidence and mortality in Auckland, 1981-6.
PG  - 479-81
AB  - Age standardised incidence and mortality rates were calculated for breast cancer 
      for the Auckland area. Incidence of female breast cancer for 1981-4 was 
      significantly higher in Auckland compared with all New Zealand, with a 
      standardised incidence ratio of 1.11. While total incidence was the same across 
      the three Auckland districts, there were wide discrepancies in mortality rates. 
      Women in Takapuna had a far lower risk of dying of breast cancer compared with 
      all New Zealand for 1981-6 and had a standardised mortality ratio of 0.86. 
      Central Auckland and south Auckland women had increased risks--1.10 and 1.18 
      respectively. Similar discrepancies were evident in the important 45-64 age 
      group. Possible reasons for the reported differences are discussed with 
      socioeconomic factors seeming the most likely agency.
