VI  - 73
IP  - 4
DP  - 1984 Apr
TI  - The psychological impact of immediate breast reconstruction for women with early 
      breast cancer.
PG  - 619-28
AB  - Twenty-five patients were evaluated, 13 who had immediate breast reconstruction 
      and 12 who had delayed breast reconstruction for early breast cancer. Data were 
      elicited about the psychological impact of the cancer, the mastectomy, and the 
      reconstruction. Our results support the conclusion that immediate breast 
      reconstruction is accompanied by a lower incidence of psychological morbidity 
      postoperatively, and we recommend that immediate breast reconstruction be offered 
      as an alternative to women with early breast cancer.
