DP  - 1986 Jan-Feb
TI  - Breast cancer treatment alternatives: the patient decision-making process.
PG  - 16-21
AB  - Today, a woman with breast cancer has many treatment alternatives. To undertake 
      the decision-making process, she must be provided with information, support, and 
      a health care network capable of meeting her needs. Surgeons are now faced with 
      new roles in the decision making process as the choice is no longer theirs. They 
      must be educated not only to keep up with the technical aspects of breast 
      surgery, but also to modify their behavior in order to become more flexible and 
      open-minded.
