DP  - 1985-1986
TI  - A pilot study of women's attitudes towards breast-conserving surgery with primary 
      radiation therapy for breast cancer.
PG  - 381-91
AB  - Breast-conserving surgery ("lumpectomy") with primary radiation therapy is 
      gaining acceptance as an alternative to mastectomy for breast cancer. Currently, 
      little is known about the specific immediate and long-range biopsychosocial 
      effects of breast-conserving therapy as compared to more traditional mastectomy 
      procedures. Physicians' speculations about the women who chose breast-conserving 
      treatment as opposed to mastectomy seem to have been influenced by the scientific 
      debate concerning the efficacy of this procedure. This study is a preliminary 
      investigation of the attitudes and experiences of women receiving breast-saving 
      therapy for carcinoma of the breast.
