TI  - [Cancer risk by family history--a cohort study in Kanagawa Prefecture].
PG  - 451-6
AB  - Cancer family history was studied for 43,117 subjects aged 35-79 at the occasion 
      of stomach cancer mass screening and were followed up for 5 years. 376 cases of 
      cancer were notified out of them by the linkage with records of population based 
      cancer registry covering the prefecture. Significantly elevated risk among those 
      with family history was found only for breast cancer (observed 3, expected 0.82).
