PMID- 2907731
OWN - NLM
STAT- MEDLINE
DCOM- 19890614
LR  - 20061115
IS  - 0764-4469 (Print)
IS  - 0764-4469 (Linking)
VI  - 307
IP  - 20
DP  - 1988
TI  - [The expression of c-myb is strongly associated with the presence of estrogen and 
      progesterone receptors in breast cancer].
PG  - 855-61
AB  - The c-myb gene was studied in 112 breast cancers. c-myb and estrogen receptor 
      (ER) transcripts were found in 78 (70%) and 71 (63%) cancers respectively. Of 
      these 71 ER positive cancers, 64 (90%) contained c-myb transcripts and of the 41 
      ER negative cancers, 27 (66%) did not contain c-myb mRNA. Our data show that 
      c-myb transcripts are strongly associated with ER and progesterone receptors (p 
      less than 10(-4) status in breast cancer. Thus the c-myb expression could be 
      associated with breast cancers of better prognosis and its analysis could allow a 
      better characterization of new subsets of hormono-dependent cancers responding 
      more efficiently to hormonotherapy.
