VI  - 110
IP  - 1
DP  - 1985
TI  - Seasonal variations in the frequency distribution of breast cancer in Greek women 
      according to the month of their birth.
PG  - 79-81
AB  - The frequency distribution of patients with breast cancer according to the month 
      of their birth was examined in 1,165 women comprising the total number of 
      patients recorded in our cancer registry from 1975 until the end of 1982. 
      Statistical evaluation of this material using an exact chi 2 for simple null 
      hypothesis demonstrated the existence of two high frequency peaks corresponding 
      to March and April in the spring and September in the autumn. These frequencies 
      were significantly higher (P less than 0.001) than those of the remaining months. 
      Confirmation of this finding would imply the introduction of a new variant in 
      breast cancer epidemiology.
