VI  - 45
IP  - 1
DP  - 1990 Sep
TI  - Impact of screening mammography and change in surgeons' attitudes on the pattern 
      of primary care of breast cancer at a community hospital.
PG  - 10-3
AB  - To gauge the impact of screening mammography and opinions regarding surgical 
      procedures on the pattern of primary surgical care of breast cancer, tumor 
      registry statistics from 1980-81 were compared to those from 1987 at a large 
      community hospital. Over the course of six years, there was a significant 
      increase in the proportion of patients with smaller tumors. Breast-conserving 
      procedures increased from 8% to 39% of all therapeutic surgery. However, there 
      was no change in the stage of the tumor at presentation because of an atypically 
      low incidence of nodal involvement in 1980-81.
