DP  - 1988 Aug
TI  - Acute leukaemia with t(4;11) in patients previously exposed to carcinogens.
PG  - 467-70
AB  - We report three cases of acute leukaemia with t(4;11) (q21;q23), one of them of 
      undifferentiated and the other two of lymphoid phenotype, occurring after 
      adjuvant radiochemotherapy for breast cancer (two cases) or occupational exposure 
      to radiation (one case). Although the myeloid phenotype and characteristic 
      chromosomal anomalies usually observed in secondary leukaemia were lacking, our 
      observations raise the possibility of causal relationship between exposure to 
      carcinogens and the occurrence of a leukaemia with t(4;11).
