DP  - 1987 Jun
TI  - Stimulation of expression of the human endogenous retrovirus genome by female 
      steroid hormones in human breast cancer cell line T47D.
PG  - 2059-62
AB  - Expression of the human endogenous retrovirus genome HERV-K, homologous to mouse 
      mammary tumor virus, was investigated in cultured human tumor cells. In several 
      cell lines, the HERV-K genome was expressed as an 8.8-kilobase poly(A)+ RNA which 
      appeared to be a full-size transcript of this genome. In the human breast cancer 
      cell line T47D, stimulation of HERV-K genome expression by progesterone was 
      observed after estradiol treatment.
