DP  - 1983
TI  - Drug resistance and cancer chemotherapy strategy in breast cancer.
PG  - 129-36
AB  - Evidence exists that spontaneous mutations to drug resistance are a major 
      obstacle to chemotherapeutic cure in both experimental and clinical neoplasms. 
      Analysis of this phenomenon indicates that certain treatment strategies may be 
      more effective in circumventing resistance. Initiation of adjuvant chemotherapy 
      at the earliest time feasible is such an approach. The use of combinations of 
      non-cross resistant agents is another. These methods should reduce the 
      probability that drug-resistant cells will be present at the time treatment is 
      started, and in theory should produce improved therapeutic results.
