DP  - 1989
TI  - Aneuploidy as a prognostic factor in breast cancer.
PG  - 117-20
AB  - The predictive value of nuclear DNA content in mammary carcinoma is still under 
      debate in spite of several reports indicating a relationship between DNA ploidy 
      and prognosis. The impact of differences in methodology on the evaluation of DNA 
      data is discussed, and a recent study demonstrating DNA ploidy as a statistically 
      significant prognostic variable on a prospective material of breast cancer 
      patients is presented.
