PMID- 2270482
OWN - NLM
STAT- MEDLINE
DCOM- 19910221
LR  - 20220408
IS  - 0036-8075 (Print)
IS  - 0036-8075 (Linking)
VI  - 250
IP  - 4988
DP  - 1990 Dec 21
TI  - Linkage of early-onset familial breast cancer to chromosome 17q21.
PG  - 1684-9
AB  - Human breast cancer is usually caused by genetic alterations of somatic cells of 
      the breast, but occasionally, susceptibility to the disease is inherited. Mapping 
      the genes responsible for inherited breast cancer may also allow the 
      identification of early lesions that are critical for the development of breast 
      cancer in the general population. Chromosome 17q21 appears to be the locale of a 
      gene for inherited susceptibility to breast cancer in families with early-onset 
      disease. Genetic analysis yields a lod score (logarithm of the likelihood ratio 
      for linkage) of 5.98 for linkage of breast cancer susceptibility to D17S74 in 
      early-onset families and negative lod scores in families with late-onset disease. 
      Likelihood ratios in favor of linkage heterogeneity among families ranged between 
      2000:1 and greater than 10(6):1 on the basis of multipoint analysis of four loci 
      in the region.
