DP  - 1984 Aug
TI  - Breast cancer concepts.
PG  - 195-200
AB  - Surgery is the primary treatment for early breast cancer. Several studies have 
      shown that routine postoperative radiation therapy does not increase patient 
      survival. Chemotherapy is currently recommended as an adjuvant to mastectomy in 
      patients with positive axillary nodes. Patients who have recurrent disease and 
      tumors that are hormone-receptor-negative, or tumors that are unresponsive and 
      hormone-receptor-positive, are receiving significant survival benefits from 
      combination chemotherapy.
