DP  - 1988 Feb
TI  - Amplification of the int-2 gene in primary human breast tumors.
PG  - 285-91
AB  - Proviral activation of the int-2 gene is a frequent occurrence in mammary 
      carcinomas induced by mouse mammary tumor virus (MMTV). Here, we have examined 
      the human homolog of int-2 in 110 primary breast cancer DNAs. The locus was 
      amplified 2- to 15-fold in 18 of the tumor DNA samples. Amplification of int-2 
      has a highly significant association (P less than 2 X 10(-6] with tumors from 
      patients who subsequently developed a local recurrence of the disease or a distal 
      metastasis.
