TI  - Social environment and breast cancer. A cohort analysis of patient survival.
PG  - 1546-50
AB  - Several crude indicators of social stress and social involvement were used to 
      explain survival among 283 women with breast cancer. The relationships of some 
      stress and involvement indicators to survival are apparent; the data provide 
      evidence that social stress decreases and social involvement increases the length 
      of time breast cancer patients survive.
