DP  - 1990 Jul
TI  - Chromosomal abnormalities in human breast cancer.
PG  - 35-43
AB  - This review emphasizes cytogenetic changes and DNA analyses by Southern blot in 
      primary breast tumors, rather than metastases, established cell lines, and 
      pleural effusions. The data suggests that the most frequently altered chromosomes 
      and chromosome regions are 1p, 1q, 2q, 3p, 5, 6q, 8p, 8q, 11p, 11q, 12, 13q, 14q, 
      16, 17p, and 17q. Changes on 8q, 11p, 11q, 13q, and 17q appear to be associated 
      with either progression of the disease or poor prognosis. Alterations on 1p and 
      3p may represent early events in the development of breast cancer.
