DP  - 1987 May
TI  - Modulation of natural killer cell activity by tamoxifen in stage I 
      post-menopausal breast cancer.
PG  - 517-20
AB  - Tamoxifen, an antiestrogen which competes for the estrogen receptor, modulates 
      natural killer cell activity in vivo. Seventeen post-menopausal stage I breast 
      cancer patients received tamoxifen for 1 month and a statistically significant 
      increase in NK activity was demonstrated (P = 0.0005). There was a small 
      incremental shift in the number of Leu-11b positive cells. These data demonstrate 
      that tamoxifen functions as a biological response modifier.
