IS  - 0301-0163 (Linking)
VI  - 32 Suppl 1
DP  - 1989
TI  - Oncogene organisation and expression: prediction in breast cancer.
PG  - 250-3
AB  - The aim of the present study was to identify genes whose expression and/or 
      organisation are altered in the diseased breast, as compared to the normal 
      breast. Alteration of one or more genes examined has been found to occur in over 
      60% of breast tumour samples. Changes to three cellular proto-oncogenes are 
      frequent, and amplification of two of these genes correlates with poor short-term 
      prognosis. Deletion of RB-1, a tumour suppressor gene, has been detected and 
      although these deletions do not correlate with poor prognosis, they occur more 
      commonly in advanced tumours. A loss of sequences encoding the progesterone 
      receptors has also been found to be frequent.
