TI  - Patient selection for prophylactic mastectomy: who is at high risk?
PG  - 324-34
AB  - Patient selection for prophylactic mastectomy should be based on an individual 
      assessment of risk factors. These should be correlated with the patient's age, 
      the difficulty of clinical examination, and, in the case of a previous breast 
      cancer, its prognosis. Only then can the patient and her surgeon make an 
      intelligent decision regarding management.
