DP  - 1987
TI  - Recurrent HSR in the centromeric region of chromosome 8 in breast cancer.
PG  - 146-51
AB  - In a sample of 44 human breast cancers, the presence of HSRs was detected in 15 
      cases (36%). The occurrence of HSRs seems correlated poorly with tumor 
      progression, but the number of HSRs per cell certainly does. Chromosome 8 was the 
      most frequently involved, and the HSRs were always located near its centromere, 
      suggesting that an amplification of gene(s) located in this region has occurred. 
      Among these, LHRH is a candidate, but further studies are needed to confirm or 
      reject this hypothesis.
