IP  - 12
DP  - 1989 Dec
TI  - Association of elevated expression of the c-erbB-2 protein with spread of breast 
      cancer.
PG  - 1192-8
AB  - We analyzed amplification and expression of the c-erbB-2 gene in human breast 
      cancers. Southern blot hybridization analysis demonstrated amplification of the 
      c-erbB-2 gene in 10 out of 50 tumor DNAs examined. The degree of amplification 
      was three- to twenty-fold relative to normal placenta. The c-erbB-2 protein could 
      be analyzed in 39 tumor tissues of the 50 samples by immuno-blotting, and 
      elevated expression of the c-erbB-2 protein was found in 15 cases. On the other 
      hand, expression of the c-erbB-2 products was not detected in normal breast 
      tissues either by immuno-blotting or by immuno-histological analysis. These data 
      indicate that transcriptional and/or translational activation of c-erbB-2 might 
      occur in some breast cancers in addition to activation by gene amplification. The 
      elevated expression of the c-erbB-2 protein was most strongly correlated with 
      lymph-node metastasis (P less than 0.001), suggesting that c-erbB-2 expression is 
      involved in promotion of the lymph-node metastasis of human breast cancers. 
      Therefore, immuno-histological diagnosis with anti-c-erbB-2 antibody might be 
      useful as an indicator to predict lymph-node involvement in breast cancer.
