TI  - [Association of major histocompatibility complex antigens (HLA antigens) and 
      breast carcinoma].
PG  - 335-40
AB  - 100 patients suffering from breast cancer and 112 healthy female blood donors 
      from Bremen have been investigated for associations between HLA antigens and this 
      disease. Altogether 58 different antigens of the HLA-A-, B- and -C-loci were 
      typed. Some associations were found regarding Bw22 and Bw55, which, however, are 
      statistically not significant.
