DP  - 1990 Dec 20
TI  - Manipulation of cell cycle kinetics: influence on the cytotoxicity of doxorubicin 
      in human breast cancer cells.
PG  - 1097-101
AB  - In vitro exposure of estrogen receptor-negative (ER-) EVSA-T human breast cancer 
      cells to insulin and/or estradiol had no effect on cell cycle distribution, in 
      contrast to a 3-5-fold increase in the percentages of cells in the S-phase of the 
      cell cycle in the ER+ MCF-7 cell line. Estrogen pretreatment of MCF-7 cells 
      followed by incubation with doxorubicin resulted in an augmented inhibition of 
      cell growth compared to unstimulated controls. This delay in growth was 
      accompanied by a decrease in the percentages of cells actively synthesizing DNA, 
      and by an augmented percentage of cells exhibiting a G2M-amount of DNA at the end 
      of a 6-9 day period of culture in complete growth medium.
