VI  - 339
DP  - 1990
TI  - Gonadotropin hormone releasing hormone agonists [GnRHA] and prevention of 
      familial breast cancer.
PG  - 193-9
AB  - The use of GnRHA to induce a "medical" oophorectomy may be a useful method of 
      prevention of breast carcinoma. The addition of ERT and intermittent progestogen 
      to the GnRHA would be expected to prevent the adverse effects of estrogen 
      deprivation, and still provide a significant reduction in breast cancer risk. 
      Evaluation of the regimen in a high risk group such as sisters or daughters of 
      index cases of early onset breast cancer is justifiable.
