DP  - 1988 Dec 15
TI  - Immunohistochemical distribution of c-erbB-2 in infiltrating and in situ breast 
      cancer.
PG  - 842-5
AB  - An immunohistochemical study of c-erbB-2 expression was performed on invasive and 
      in situ breast cancer. Strong membrane staining was seen in 16% of the 
      infiltrating ductal carcinomas and 44% of the in situ lesions. c-erbB-2 was 
      overexpressed in ductal rather than lobular tumours. Our results indicate that a 
      small sub-group of breast carcinomas are associated with over-expression of this 
      oncogene which may define an important subgroup of in situ and infiltrating 
      ductal carcinomas.
