TI  - The role of the epidermal growth factor receptor and the c-erbB-2 protein in 
      breast cancer.
PG  - 55-61
AB  - Breast cancer cells are derived from epithelial cells lining the ducts of the 
      breast. One of the fundamental characteristics that distinguish tumour cells from 
      normal cells is that cancer cells grow in an apparently unregulated way. 
      Understanding the mechanisms that regulate the growth and differentiation of 
      normal breast epithelial cells and the differences between these systems in 
      cancer cells is one of the central goals of research into the cell biology of 
      breast cancer.
