IS  - 0006-291X (Linking)
VI  - 128
IP  - 2
DP  - 1985 Apr 30
TI  - MDA-468, a human breast cancer cell line with a high number of epidermal growth 
      factor (EGF) receptors, has an amplified EGF receptor gene and is growth 
      inhibited by EGF.
PG  - 898-905
AB  - Epidermal growth factor (EGF) has been noted to stimulate proliferation of a 
      variety of normal and malignant cells including those of human breast epithelium. 
      We report here that MDA-468, a human breast cancer cell line with a very high 
      number of EGF receptors, is growth-inhibited at EGF concentrations that stimulate 
      most other cells. The basis for the elevated receptor level is EGF receptor gene 
      amplification and over-expression. An MDA-468 clone selected for resistance to 
      EGF-induced growth inhibition shows a number of receptors within the normal 
      range. The results are discussed in relation to a threshold model for EGF-induced 
      growth inhibition.
