TI  - Redefined indications for subcutaneous mastectomy in patients with benign breast 
      disease.
PG  - 101-4
AB  - The indications for subcutaneous mastectomy have been redefined as a result of 
      more recent and more conclusive data. This information has provided us with 
      specific biological markers that define more clearly the high-risk woman for 
      breast cancer. Proliferative disease, with and without atypia, should replace the 
      previous criterion of moderate to severe fibrocystic disease or non-specific 
      mammary dysplasia.
