DP  - 1986 Oct
TI  - Cowden disease. A hereditary polyposis syndrome diagnosable by mucocutaneous 
      inspection.
PG  - 576-9
AB  - Cowden disease (multiple harmartoma syndrome) is of particular interest because 
      the diagnostic mucocutaneous findings are coupled with a striking association of 
      thyroid cancer, breast cancer, and polyposis of the gastrointestinal tract. We 
      report a case of Cowden disease with particular emphasis on the natural history 
      of the case. Although our case is the second reported with colon carcinoma, the 
      absence of adenomatous polyps in other reports of Cowden disease and the 
      stability of the gastrointestinal polyps in our patient over a seven-year period 
      lead us to conclude that the risk of gastrointestinal malignancy is very low.
