DP  - 1982 Feb
TI  - Breast masses in adolescents.
PG  - 141-5
AB  - The most common pubertal breast masses are gynecomastia in boys and breast buds 
      in girls. Gynecomastia usually resolves spontaneously in one or two years. Breast 
      buds must never be biopsied or excised. Fibroadenomas are the most common benign 
      breast tumors in adolescent girls. Breast cancer in this age group is rare but 
      possible. Careful observation over one or two menstrual cycles is recommended, 
      followed by an excisional biopsy if an undiagnosed breast lesion persists.
