DP  - 1988 Oct 15
TI  - A unique pattern of proto-oncogene abnormalities in ovarian adenocarcinomas.
PG  - 1573-6
AB  - Twelve cases of ovarian adenocarcinoma were studied for alterations in 
      proto-oncogenes, and a unique pattern of altered ras proto-oncogenes was 
      observed. Amplification of ras-Ki was found in three of seven ovarian tumors and 
      amplification of ras-Ha in one of 12. In contrast, ras-Ha amplification was not 
      found in any of the 334 other tumors and ras-Ki amplification was only seen in 
      breast cancer at a frequency of 3%. Other proto-oncogenes altered in ovarian 
      adenocarcinomas included c-myc and c-erbb-2. Proto-oncogene abnormalities were 
      more frequent in aggressive tumors of high histologic grade.
