TI  - Torre-Muir syndrome. An association with isolated sebaceous carcinoma.
PG  - 2868-73
AB  - Three cases of Torre-Muir syndrome are described in which isolated sebaceous 
      carcinomas were associated with internal malignancy. The first was a 66-year-old 
      woman who had a sebaceous carcinoma in association with carcinoma of the uterus, 
      two adenocarcinomas of colon, carcinoma of renal pelvis and bladder, and a 
      squamous cell carcinoma of the skin. The second was a 78-year-old woman who had a 
      sebaceous carcinoma associated with carcinomas of the colon, ovary, and pancreas. 
      The third patient had a sebaceous carcinoma associated with breast cancer. The 
      subject is discussed and the previously reported cases reviewed.
