TI  - Lobular carcinoma of the breast in a patient with Klinefelter's syndrome. A case 
      with bilateral, synchronous, histologically different breast tumors.
PG  - 1181-3
AB  - A case of bilateral breast cancer in a patient with a Klinefelter mosaic syndrome 
      is presented. The tumor in the left breast was an infiltrating lobular carcinoma 
      with characteristic in situ component. To the knowledge of the authors, this is 
      the first case in the English literature of lobular carcinoma of the breast in a 
      phenotypic man. In fact, it was the pathologic diagnosis which led to the study 
      of the chromosomal abnormality.
