DP  - 1989 Jan 15
TI  - Rare clonal karyotypic variants in primary cultures of human breast carcinoma 
      cells.
PG  - 444-9
AB  - Cytogenetic analyses were performed on 40 previously untreated primary human 
      breast carcinomas, four untreated breast metastases, nine human breast 
      fibroadenomas, and ten normal human mammary tissues, all in primary culture. The 
      results revealed predominantly normal diploid cells with abnormal clones in two 
      of 40 primary carcinomas and one of four metastases. 3p deletion 
      [del(3)(p14-21)], similar to that associated with small cell lung cancer, was 
      found in a primary tumor from a patient with bilateral breast cancer. In 
      addition, a clone with t(1;4) was found in another primary breast carcinoma, 
      while a t(1;5) clone was found in a metastatic tumor.
