VI  - 215
IP  - 4540
DP  - 1982 Mar 26
TI  - Legal abortion: the public health record.
PG  - 1586-90
AB  - The increasing availability and utilization of legal abortion in the United 
      States has several important effects on public health in the 1970's. It reduced 
      deaths and surgical complications among women of childbearing age; it made 
      possible the development of safer surgical procedures for pregnancy termination; 
      and it increased the provision of low-cost outpatient gynecologic services. There 
      is some concern about potential adverse outcomes in future desired pregnancies 
      and possibly higher risks of breast cancer in certain women.
