OAB - Public health in the United States has been affected in the past decade by the 
      increased availability and utilization of abortion. The legalization of abortion 
      has led to a decrease in deaths and surgical complications among women of 
      childbearing age, the development of safer procedures for pregnancy termination, 
      and the provision of low-cost outpatient services. Adverse outcomes in future 
      pregnancies and an increase in breast cancer risk are two of the possible 
      negative results of the increased abortion rate. Three graphs and a statistical 
      table illustrate the article.
